result.formatted_address: 18/F, 99 Percival St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Sorabol Korean Restaurant

reviews.text: Staffs are nice, food is good. Like many other traditional Korean restaurants, their appetizers are unlimited. Seafood pancake is okay, the soup is nice. The meat is the best part still. xD

Service was slow, staff seemed stressed. Most dishes, not including BBQ, were around $110-140 hk. A bit pricey for what it is. The tables were nice and the place seemed new-ish. It's in a mall so the bathroom is outside the restaurant.

Quite a good Korean restaurant that covers all the basics quite well. The menu has all the Korean BBQ options you would expect pork, beef, chicken etc. along with some interesting stews that also go on the BBQ plate.

This is a dependable Korean restaurant. It's fairly popular,  but you are usually able to get a table even without a booking.

Lunch from this Korean restaurant is great.
The food here is good, and it's a decent and in traditional style.  They have a big window, so you enjoy the Korean food with view of Causeway Bay.
As in other Korean restaurant, they provide refill on side dishes, and they taste great too.
Price here is reasonable, although it's in premium location, but lunch is only about $100 per person

Very decent lunch menu. The lunch sets were mostly under $100. The dishes were well made and very flavoursome. Also, I love their sides dishes which can be refilled. The portion was definitely enough for lunch. Great food, great ambience and reasonable price, what more can you ask for.

reviews.text: 한국말을 하는 직원분이 계셔서 좋았구요. 김치찌개 맛있어요. 불고기덮밥도 맛있구요. 둘이서 점심메뉴 2개 시켰는데 양이 살짝 많은 느낌. 밑빈찬도 정갈하니 맛있어요. 향신료에 지쳤던 터라 정신없이 먹었더니 사진도 못찍었네요. 조용히 여유롭게 먹었습니다. 층수가 높아서 창가쪽 경치도 좋아요.

result.formatted_address: 99號, Percival St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Lee Theatre

reviews.text: This area of Hong Kong was recently redone. The shopping area is really cute with tons of stores. It is very clean the sales people are very helpful it's a few blocks away from times square mall. It's has lots of up  scale stores they are all very nice there is multiple buildings in the Lee Theater area so check the address to make sure you are in the correct building

Large shopping mall which is part of the Lee Gardens concept. Nice and functional, but not really with to much of a soul of is own or anything else to do really than to shop and eat. Functional rather than fantastic.

Your dinning place. Lots of nice restaurants in this building. 

Lower level are clothing shops. Upper levels are all restaurants. Take the lifts to go up to the higher levels.

this is a place to visit especially if you love shopping at UNIQLO. Several floors of UNIQLO assures you way better variety and stocks. Being located in causeway bay, it is convenient to explore from one shopping mall to another since the malls are just adjacent to each other.
The once iconic landmark theater turned shopping and dining center.
